# Cursor Project Rules: TCC Modeler (CF Model App)

## Project purpose

This app is a TCC/CF Modeler for physician compensation. It is used by compensation administrators to:

- Upload provider and market survey data (CSV or XLSX) with optional column mapping.
- Run single-provider scenarios (provider → scenario → market → results) and batch scenarios across all providers.
- Use the CF Optimizer and Productivity Target tools for specialty-level modeling.
- View reports (saved runs, TCC/wRVU percentiles, impact, quick-run CF, custom CF by specialty, market positioning).
- Export results to XLSX and CSV (no DOCX/PDF or contract generation in this app).

Data and scenarios live in browser memory and localStorage; there is no backend.

---

## Tech stack and tools

- React 18+ with TypeScript and Vite
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui (Radix primitives)
- Recharts for charts
- PapaParse (CSV) and SheetJS (xlsx) for file parsing and export
- Vitest for unit tests
- State: React state + custom hooks (use-app-state, use-provider-actions, etc.) — no Redux
- Persistence: localStorage via lib/storage.ts, lib/batch-storage.ts, lib/optimizer-storage.ts, lib/productivity-target-storage.ts
- Web Workers for batch and optimizer runs (workers/batch-worker.ts, workers/optimizer-worker.ts)

---

## Folder structure

Keep feature code under src/features/; do not put feature-specific code in src/ root.

```
src/
├── components/     # Shared UI (layout, upload/mapping, batch flows, charts, ui/)
├── features/
│   ├── data/           # Provider/market tables, edit modals
│   ├── optimizer/      # CF optimizer, compare scenarios, imputed-vs-market
│   ├── productivity-target/
│   ├── reports/        # Report library, saved runs, TCC/wRVU reports
│   └── help/           # Help screen, wizards
├── hooks/         # use-app-state, use-provider-actions, use-batch-actions, etc.
├── lib/           # Compute, parse-file, storage, engines, *-export.ts
├── types/         # provider, market, scenario, batch, optimizer, upload
├── utils/         # format, math, aggregate-fte, sample-upload
└── workers/       # batch-worker, optimizer-worker
```

---

## Data and column mapping

- Provider file: one row per provider; expected columns in types/provider.ts. Headers are mapped on upload via ColumnMapping in types/upload.ts.
- Market file: one row per specialty with percentile columns (e.g. TCC_25–TCC_90, WRVU_25–WRVU_90). See types/market.ts and lib/parse-file.ts.
- Mapping/parsing: lib/parse-file.ts — buildDefaultProviderMapping / buildDefaultMarketMapping, applyProviderMapping / applyMarketMapping. Validation errors are returned as errors: string[] and shown in the upload UI.

---

## Export and outputs

- Exports are XLSX and CSV only (no DOCX/PDF). See lib/single-scenario-export.ts, lib/batch-export.ts, and other *-export.ts in lib/.
- Batch/scenario results are exported as wide rows with match status, risk, percentiles, and governance flags (e.g. fmvCheckSuggested).

---

## Governance and FMV

- FMV risk is computed from TCC percentiles (e.g. lib/optimizer-constants.ts: FMV_RED_FLAG_PERCENTILE, getFmvRiskLevel).
- UI shows "FMV check suggested" and risk levels via components/governance-flags.tsx and optimizer/report tables.
- An audit log for FMV-related overrides can be added in lib/audit.ts (non-PII only) if needed.

---

## Code practices

- Use existing hooks for state and persistence; do not add Redux unless the roadmap requires it.
- Keep compute/engine logic in lib/; keep UI in components/ and features/.
- Use types from src/types/ for provider, market, scenario, batch, optimizer, and upload.
- For new validation or persisted data, consider zod for DTOs and localStorage load validation.
- Use the shared LoadingState component and Error Boundaries for async and render errors.

---

## File naming

- camelCase for variables and functions
- PascalCase for components
- kebab-case for filenames (e.g. upload-and-mapping.tsx, optimizer-configure-stage.tsx)
- Use .tsx only for files with JSX; use .ts for pure logic

---

## Testing

- Unit tests (Vitest) live next to the code (e.g. lib/compute.test.ts, lib/optimizer-engine.test.ts). Add tests for new engines and for parse-file / mapping when changing validation or column handling.
